Paper: hep-th/9204069

Date: 1992-04-22

Title: Ashtekar's Variables for Arbitrary Gauge Group

Authors: Peter Peldan

Comments: 6pp

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D46 (1992) 2279-2282

A generally covariant gauge theory for an arbitrary gauge group withdimension $\geq 3$, that reduces to Ashtekar's canonical formulation of gravityfor SO(3,C), is presented. The canonical form of the theory is shown to containonly first class constraints.